                            <comment id="98287" author="sbrannen" created="Fri, 31 Jan 2014 13:38:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue duplicates &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-6121&quot; title=&quot;Dependency injection of @Configurable objects should work across test suites&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-6121&quot;&gt;SPR-6121&lt;/a&gt;, with regard to support for &lt;tt&gt;@Configurable&lt;/tt&gt; across test classes within a test suite.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding not properly closing a context after a test class has finished, this is in fact by design and one of the key features of the Spring TestContext Framework (TCF). Namely, the TCF caches contexts across all test methods and test classes within a test suite unless a test method or test class is explicitly configured with &lt;tt&gt;@DirtiesContext&lt;/tt&gt;. For details on caching support in the TCF, please refer to the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/3.2.x/spring-framework-reference/html/testing.html#testcontext-ctx-management-caching&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Context caching&lt;/a&gt; section of the reference manual.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
